<DOC><DOCNO> WSJ881115-0115 </DOCNO><HL> Bernard Chaus Inc. Posts Loss </HL><SO> </SO><CO> CHS </CO><IN> ERN </IN><DATELINE> NEW YORK  </DATELINE><TEXT>   Bernard Chaus Inc. reported a net loss for its first quarter ended Oct. 1 but predicted &quot;a meaningful improvement&quot; in the fiscal second quarter.    The women's-sportswear maker said the loss was $5.3 million, compared with net income of $2.8 million, or 15 cents a share, a year earlier. Sales fell 34% to $61.3 million from $92.9 million.    Bernard Chaus, chairman, blamed the loss on a decrease in units sold and on reduced prices. He based his outlook for the current quarter on &quot;shipments to date and trends in current bookings.&quot;    In New York Stock Exchange composite trading yesterday Chaus shares declined 12.5 cents to $3.875. </TEXT></DOC>